      "citation_count": 3,
      "latency_seconds": 6.18,
      "answer": "The decision on whether packaging data should become separate article records is made by the business owner and logistics owner during the identification of the packaging use case [1]. Specifically, the business first decides whether the packaging topic is operational tracking, downstream planning information, or regulatory reporting. This categorization helps in determining how to model the packaging data, including whether it should be part of separate article records or handled as attributes or listing fields [3] [4].\n\nThe evidence does not specify a single role but indicates that both business and logistics owners are involved in this initial categorization decision [1]."
